                            }
                        ]
                    ],
                    "wrapper": {
                        "width": "",
                        "class": "tip",
                        "id": ""
                    },
                    "message": "Start by assigning relevant parent categories.\r\n\r\nIf the entire resource covers a single topic (EG: guidance to use an app) you should assign any relevant sub-categories on the intro\/parent page.\r\n\r\nIf the resource covers a variety of topics (EG: the carers checklist includes advice on finance, leisure, home alterations) you should ONLY assign the  parent categories on the intro\/parent page.  Specific sub-categories can be assigned on the relevant sub pages",
                    "new_lines": "wpautop",
                    "esc_html": 0
                },
                {
                    "key": "field_5ba371c98bc1d",
                    "label": "For Sub Pages",
                    "name": "",
                    "type": "message",
                    "instructions": "",
                    "required": 0,
                    "conditional_logic": [
                        [
                            {
                                "field": "field_5ba370be8bc1a",
                                "operator": "==",
                                "value": "Sub-page of a multi-page resource"
                            }
                        ]
                    ],
                    "wrapper": {
                        "width": "",
                        "class": "tip",
                        "id": ""
                    },
                    "message": "Firstly, choose your parent page from the drop-down list in the <strong>Page Attributes<\/strong> box to the right.  Also, enter the page number into the <strong>Order<\/strong> text field.\r\n\r\nIf the entire resource covers a single topic (EG: guidance to use an app) you DO NOT need to assign any categories to sub pages. You should assign relevant categories\/sub-categories on the intro\/parent page of the resource.\r\n \r\nIf the resource covers a variety of topics (EG: the carers checklist includes advice on finance, leisure, home alterations) you should assign the relevant sub-categories here.",
